<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="necessity-n">necessity <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /nə'sesəti/    美 /nə'sesəti/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-u">1.★ <strong>[U] 必要 (性)；需要：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We were discussing <strong>the necessity of</strong> employing more staff. 
当时我们正在讨论是否有必要雇佣更多的员工。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We took the country road <strong>out of necessity</strong>.
出于需要我们走了乡间小路。</p><footer>2013 天津</footer></div>

<h4 id="2c">2.<strong>[C] 必需品；必要之物：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>For many Americans the automobile is a necessity.
对于很多美国人来说，汽车是必需品。</p></div></div>